'''Marco Fassone''' (born August 17, 1964 in Pinerolo) is an Italian business executive and sports manager, former managing director of [[AC Milan]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.acmilan.com/it/news/intervista/2017-07-21/fassone-vi-racconto-i-miei-primi-100-giorni-rossoneri|title=FASSONE: "VI RACCONTO I MIEI PRIMI 100 GIORNI ROSSONERI" - AC Milan|first=AC|last=Milan|website=AC Milan}}</ref> He assumed this role after [[Li Yonghong|Li Yonghong’s]] Luxembourg-based holding company, Rossoneri Sport Investment, completed the takeover of Milan from Italian media mogul and former prime minister [[Silvio Berlusconi]].<ref>{{cite web|title=Milan’s Chinese owners take high-risk gamble in search of lost glories|url=https://www.theguardian.com/football/blog/2017/aug/27/milan-china-owners-champions-league-debts-us-equity-fund}}</ref>

He has previously held leadership positions at other football clubs, most notably, [[Juventus]], [[Napoli Football|Napoli]] and [[Inter Milan]].<ref>{{cite web|title=Who is Marco Fassone: the man who is going to put an end to Galliani’s reign at AC Milan|url=http://www.calciomercato.com/en/news/who-is-marco-fassone-the-man-who-is-going-to-put-an-end-to-galli-175681}}</ref>

